# Hyphen punctuation

In all user-facing text (UI copy, alt text, comments meant for readability, meta descriptions, commit messages when user-facing):

- Use hyphen `-` only
- Never use em dash `—` or en dash `–`

Examples:
- Good: `AI/ML Engineer - Software Developer`
- Bad: `AI/ML Engineer — Software Developer`

Loading placeholders: use `-` not `—`.
